<BaseLayout>
  <h1>Welcome to your Dashboard</h1>
  <p>This is your home base — your campaign starts here.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>🪵 What is Page Zero?</h2>
    <p><strong>Page Zero</strong> helps you set the stage before your campaign even begins — fleshing out characters, relationships, and session 0 decisions with ease. Think of this as your adventurer’s journal, storyteller’s toolkit, and memory keeper all rolled into one.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>📜 Sidebar Guide</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>🏠 <strong>Dashboard</strong> – You’re here! Your launch point and quick reference hub.</li>
      <li>🧍 <strong>Characters</strong> – Create, view, and edit your PCs and NPCs with detailed sheets.</li>
      <li>⚙️ <strong>Session 0</strong> – Answer session zero questions, establish group dynamics, and build your party's origin.</li>
      <li>🔗 <strong>Relationships</strong> – Map out character bonds, rivalries, romances, and history with visual clarity.</li>
      <li>📜 <strong>Logs</strong> – Record major story events, notes from each session, and player discoveries.</li>
      <li>⬇️ <strong>Downloads</strong> – Export filled PDFs, relationship maps, or full campaign archives when you're ready.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>✨ Get Started</h2>
    <p>Pick a section on the left to begin. We recommend starting with <strong>Session 0</strong> to define your party’s world and rules.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
